Class QuestionAnswerPoliticObj

  • java.lang.Object
    • data.QuestionAnswerPoliticObj
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class QuestionAnswerPoliticObj
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Java provides a mechanism, called object serialization where an object can be represented as a sequence of bytes that includes the object's data as well as information about the object's type and the types of data stored in the object. After a serialized object has been written into a file, it can be read from the file and deserialized that is, the type information and bytes that represent the object and its data can be used to recreate the object in memory. This is model class used for create the object which contain questionID, question text, answer from anonymous user and answer from politician used in GetResults_detail.java service
